If I understand correctly, it loads correctly the first time, then following attempts to show a different modal are just showing the same modal with the same data.

This is most likely because you are not using a unique `id` for the modal. The first modal that gets added to the DOM with the `id=&quot;details-modal&quot;` is the only one that is found by `jQuery(&#39;#details-modal&#39;)` so it will be that same modal that is shown each time. You could remove the modal from the DOM when it&#39;s closed but, you end up repeating ajax calls you have already made when a user re-opens a modal they closed. 

Consider adding the `$row-&gt;id` to the `id` of the returned modal i.e.`id=&quot;details-modal-4&quot;`, then in your javascript  function start by checking to see if you already have the specific modal you need, if not then make the ajax call to get it.

    function detailsmodal(id) {
        var thisModal = jQuery(&#39;#details-modal-&#39; + id);
        if(thisModal.length){
            thisModal.modal(&#39;toggle&#39;);
        }else{
            var data = {&quot;id&quot; : id};
            // send data to store_items/detailsmodal
            jQuery.ajax({
                url     : &#39;&lt;?= base_url()?&gt;store_items/detailsmodal&#39;,
                method  : &quot;post&quot;,
                data    : data,
                success : function(data){
                    jQuery(&#39;body&#39;).append(data);
                    jQuery(&#39;#details-modal-&#39; + id).modal(&#39;toggle&#39;);
    
    
                },
                error   : function(){
                    alert(&quot;Something went wrong!&quot;);
                }
            });
        }
    }

